<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Mutsu</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-03-12"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 12,
                                1889</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to our conversation of this
                            afternoon, I take pleasure in now informing you that provision has been
                            made for paying $15,000 to your Government, as indemnity for injuries
                            caused to Japanese subjects by explosion of shells from the United
                            States steamer <hi rend="italic">Omaha.</hi></p>
                        <p>Measures will at once be taken to effect this payment at an early
                            day.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>